Conjecture

Let P_m(x)=2^{-m}\cdot((x-\sqrt{x^2-4})^{m}+(x+\sqrt{x^2-4})^{m}) . 
Let N=k \cdot b^n-1 such that k>0 , 3 \not\mid k , k<2^n , b>0 , b is even number, 3 \not\mid b  and n > 2 . 
Let S_i=P_b(S_{i-1}) with S_0=P_{kb/2}(P_{b/2}(4)) , then 
N is a prime if and only if S_{n-2} \equiv 0\pmod{N} .
